The paper deals with the verification of message passing programs, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of bounded analysis and k-synchronous computations suggests a focus on programming languages and semantics (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The exploration of reachability and decidability of k-synchronizability points towards algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY).
